                    <span>i found the ideas in this book fascinating and intriguing. entertaining for sure, to say the least. some of the ideas in this book may not be new, but its new to me. i guess you can say it opened my eyes a bit more and perhaps broadened my horizons. reading this book was a lot better than going thru pages of research, which for me, is much too boring. i usually just read the abstracts and conclusions. if it were interesting enough i will plow thru the data as well. but that is quite seldom for me. in any case, its definitely a good book. call it twisting, repackaging, and whatever. but it served me well by being written and presented in a language most of us can understand and relate to without being too technical about everything.. what more can i say??</span>
                  
